headline.main: SPY SUSPECT TELLS OF DYNAMITE PLOT; Testifies FBI Agent Urged Him to 'Put It in Roosevelt's Church in Hyde Park'

lead_paragraph: Frederick Joubert Duquesne testified yesterday at the Brooklyn espionage trial that he had informed the Federal Bureau of Investigation that William G. Sebold, counter-espionage agent for the FBI and principal government witness, was a "dangerous lunatic" because he had urged Duquesne to "put dynamite in President Roosevelt's church in Hyde Park."
abstract: F J Duquesne, Bklyn espionage suspect, charges counter-espionage agent offered him funds for Madison Sq Garden rally contribution
